Check how many top-scoring (top 330) EC pairs are satisfied in the 5oqt_A model at 5 and 8 Angstrom distance thresholds¶

In [13]:
cc_5oqt_8A = coupling_scores_compared(
    ecs, dm_5oqt,
    dist_cutoff=8,
)

cc_5oqt_5A = coupling_scores_compared(
    ecs, dm_5oqt,
    dist_cutoff=5,
)

print('Fraction of top 330 ECs satisfied within 5A: {}'.format(len(cc_5oqt_5A.head(330).query('dist <= 5'))/330))
print('Fraction of top 330 ECs satisfied within 8A: {}'.format(len(cc_5oqt_5A.head(330).query('dist <= 8'))/330))

Fraction of top 330 ECs satisfied within 5A: 0.5121212121212121
Fraction of top 330 ECs satisfied within 8A: 0.8545454545454545

Generate Supp. Fig. 12a, a complex contact map showing highest-scoring ECs between GerAA and GerAB¶

In [11]:
# Load EC data
c_ecs = pd.read_csv('../data/GERAA_GERAB_complex/GerAA_b01_GerAB_b03_gd_CouplingScoresCompared_longrange.csv')

# Take top 20 inter-ECs 
c_ecs_subset = c_ecs.head(343)
c_ecs_inter = c_ecs_subset.query('segment_i != segment_j')
c_ecs_A = c_ecs_subset.query('(segment_i == "A_1") and (segment_j == "A_1")')
c_ecs_B = c_ecs_subset.query('(segment_i == "B_1") and (segment_j == "B_1")')

# Load in homologous structures for comparison
dm_first_monomer = DistanceMap.from_file('../data/GERAA_GERAB_complex/GerAA_b01_GerAB_b03_gd_first_distance_map_monomer')
dm_first_multimer = DistanceMap.from_file('../data/GERAA_GERAB_complex/GerAA_b01_GerAB_b03_gd_first_distance_map_multimer')

# Offer different marker sizes for structural and predicted contacts - 
# you can change these which of these options is used in the complex_contact_map() function below.
STYLE_EC_110 = {
    "edgecolor": "none",
    "c": "black",
    "s": 110,
}

STYLE_CONTACT_190 = {
    "edgecolor": "none",
    "c": "#b6d4e9",
    "s": 190,
}

STYLE_CONTACT_MULTIMER_190 = {
    "edgecolor": "none",
    "c": "#fc8c3b",
    "alpha": 0.3,
    "s": 190,
}

# Call our function to plot complex contact maps
#ec_style=STYLE_EC, monomer_style=STYLE_CONTACT,multimer_style=STYLE_CONTACT_MULTIMER,
with plot_context("Arial"):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    
    complex_contact_map(c_ecs_A, c_ecs_B, c_ecs_inter,
                        d_intra_i=dm_first_monomer, d_multimer_i=dm_first_multimer, d_intra_j=None, d_multimer_j=None, d_inter=None, boundaries='union', ec_style=STYLE_EC_110, monomer_style=STYLE_CONTACT_190, multimer_style=STYLE_CONTACT_MULTIMER_190)
